---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceExplore from '../../components/ServiceExplore.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Emergency Dentistry — Oasis Dental Care, Huntington Beach"
  description="Same-day emergency dental care in Huntington Beach. Toothaches, broken teeth, and infections seen quickly by Dr. Jason Fu. Call (714) 893-2106."
  page="services"
>

<section class="phero">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumbs"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/services">Services</a><span class="sep">/</span><span style="color:#cfe6e2">Emergency Dentistry</span></div>
    <span class="tag">Emergency care</span>
    <h1>Emergency Dentistry</h1>
    <p>Fast relief when you need it most.</p>
    <div class="acts">
      <a class="btn" href="tel:7148932106">Call (714) 893-2106 <svg class="ico" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M5 12h14M13 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg></a>
      <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/contact">Request appointment</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="pad">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="split">
      <div>

        <div class="img-ph reveal">
          <div class="img-ph-ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="9" r="1.5"/><path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/></svg></div>
          <span class="img-ph-lbl">Photo placeholder</span>
          <span class="img-ph-desc">Calm, reassuring office; front desk phone or open door — suggests urgency without alarm</span>
        </div>

        <div class="prose reveal">
          <span class="tag">Overview</span>
          <h2>We hold time daily for urgent dental needs.</h2>
          <p>Toothache, broken teeth, dental infection, or trauma—we set aside time each day for urgent needs so you can get seen quickly and avoid unnecessary worry.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="prose reveal" style="margin-top:48px">
          <h3>What Counts as a Dental Emergency?</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Severe or persistent toothache</li>
            <li>Broken, chipped, or knocked-out tooth</li>
            <li>Swollen jaw or signs of infection</li>
            <li>Lost crown or filling causing pain</li>
            <li>Soft-tissue injury (gums, tongue, lip)</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="img-ph reveal">
            <div class="img-ph-ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="9" r="1.5"/><path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/></svg></div>
            <span class="img-ph-lbl">Photo placeholder</span>
            <span class="img-ph-desc">Calm patient being reassured by staff at front desk</span>
          </div>

          <h3>What to Do First</h3>
          <p>Call us immediately at (714) 893-2106. We hold daily appointment slots for urgent cases. For a knocked-out tooth, keep it moist (milk or saliva) and bring it with you.</p>

          <h3>What to Expect</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Same-day or next-available urgent slot</li>
            <li>Immediate pain assessment and relief</li>
            <li>Digital imaging to diagnose the cause</li>
            <li>Clear explanation of treatment options before anything begins</li>
          </ul>

          <div class="img-ph reveal">
            <div class="img-ph-ic"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="3"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="9" r="1.5"/><path d="m21 15-5-5L5 21"/></svg></div>
            <span class="img-ph-lbl">Photo placeholder</span>
            <span class="img-ph-desc">Dr. Fu calmly examining patient; compassionate, reassuring tone</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="reveal" style="margin-top:48px">
          <span class="tag">Common questions</span>
          <h2 class="prose" style="margin-top:8px">Good to know.</h2>
          <div class="faq">
            <details open><summary>What counts as a dental emergency?</summary><p>Severe pain, swelling, broken or knocked-out teeth, persistent bleeding, or any sudden change in your mouth that worries you should be treated as an emergency. If you're unsure, call us—we'll help you decide what to do next.</p></details>
            <details><summary>Can a knocked-out tooth be saved?</summary><p>Often, yes—if you act quickly. Keep the tooth moist (in milk or your cheek), avoid touching the root, and call us right away. Fast action increases the chance of saving the tooth.</p></details>
            <details><summary>What if my dental emergency happens after hours?</summary><p>Call our office—our voicemail will give you instructions, and we do our best to respond to true emergencies as soon as possible, even after hours.</p></details>
            <details><summary>Will insurance cover emergency dental care?</summary><p>Most plans cover some emergency services. We'll check your benefits, explain costs up front, and help you find solutions if you don't have insurance.</p></details>
            <details><summary>Do I need an appointment for emergency care?</summary><p>We prioritize emergency calls and can usually see you the same day. It's best to call ahead so we can prepare for your arrival.</p></details>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <aside>
        <div class="scard reveal">
          <div class="hd"><div class="grid-ov"></div><h3>Call now for urgent care</h3><p>Same-day slots held daily for emergencies</p></div>
          <div class="bd">
            <div class="row"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="9"/><path d="M12 7v5l3 2"/></svg><span>Call early for best availability</span></div>
            <div class="row"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M20 6 9 17l-5-5"/></svg><span>Most insurance accepted &amp; verified</span></div>
            <div class="row"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M12 2 4 5v6c0 5 3.5 9 8 11 4.5-2 8-6 8-11V5l-8-3z"/></svg><span>Pain relief is our first priority</span></div>
            <div class="divider"></div>
            <a class="btn" href="tel:7148932106">Call (714) 893-2106</a>
            <a class="btn btn-out" href="/contact" style="justify-content:center">Request appointment</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<ServiceExplore />

</Layout>
